<div class="hidden"><h1>getEncryptedCookie()</h1>
		<p>To retrieve data stored in a cookie sent to the client through <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/addencryptedcookie/" target="_self">addEncryptedCookie()</a>, simply pass the $name of the cookie to <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/getencryptedcookie/" target="_self">getEncryptedCookie()</a>, and the value will be returned if it is available.</p>
		<p>Version: </p>
		<p>Method Definition: getEncryptedCookie($name)</p>
		<p>Invoking class: cookie_manager</p><h2>Technical Specifications:<h2><p>It is recommended that you upgrade to the latest version of PHP to take advantage of the latests gains in security and processing efficiency.</p><p>Currently tested on an ubuntu 4.2 server running PHP Version 5.2.6 and Apache 2.2.11</p><p>Data stored in cookies created through the invocation of <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/addcookie/" target="_self">addCookie()</a> or the <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/" target="_self">cookie_manager</a> :: class <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/__construct/" target="_self">constructor</a> cannot be retrieved via <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/getencryptedcookie/" target="_self">getEncryptedCookie()</a>. The <a href="../../../classes/cookie_manager/getencryptedcookie/" target="_self">getEncryptedCookie()</a> method will not return useful cookie data where encryption has NOT been used.</p><h2>Parameters:</h2><h3>$name</h3><p>The name of the cookie.</p><p>Last upated: 2017-04-11 02:27:21</p></div>